{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d9c2eacc-6f55-461f-ae4c-52eab91723f6","content":"The problem is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. F# compiles files top-to-bottom, so dependencies must be listed first. `Services.fs` references `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing by swapping `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_2aLwYGvoaejXQRDmyOUCQB","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d7088ff6f66c41378fca2719cd06559a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d7088ff6f66c41378fca2719cd06559a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"be71388e-a67e-4e20-b35e-5d8c1b36e7b7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order in the `.fsproj` matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed **before** them. Currently:\n\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first — it `open`s `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` comes after it.\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second.\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third — it `open`s both `Domain` and `Services`.\n\nThe fix: `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`, and both before `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":398,"requestId":"1C30:2CF140:AD95BE:CAA506:69F3FA72"},"id":"5310bbba-d505-40ed-8daf-fecb29199dfd","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:57:30.808Z","parentId":"f50adb58-dbca-4041-bfd4-f11e955b2bd8"}
